SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1131
By Hensley
A RESOLUTION to honor and recognize Brylee Whitehead, 2026
Top Ten Senior of Lewis County High School.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to pay
tribute to those students who, through their natural talents and unflagging commitment to
academic excellence, have distinguished themselves in the classroom; and
WHEREAS, Brylee Whitehead is one such exceptional student, who was recently
named a Top Ten Senior of the 2026 graduating class at Lewis County High School; and
WHEREAS, through diligent study, steady composure during examinations, and
steadfast commitment of time and talent, Ms. Whitehead has achieved outstanding academic
success and joined the ranks of the best and brightest students in Tennessee and our country;
and
WHEREAS, in her remarkable high school career, Brylee Whitehead has earned an
exemplary grade point average while participating in numerous extracurricular activities,
including Beta Club, Anchor Club, FCA, and HOSA, and serving as a CTE Ambassador and
cheerleader; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Whitehead has received several awards and accolades, including
Middle Tennessee State University True Blue 100, Congress of Future Medical Leaders
nomination, and Perfect Attendance Award for the 2024-2025 school year; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Whitehead's display of intellectual aptitude and ambition surely bodes
well for her future success and her plans to major in biochemistry and later attend medical
school; and
WHEREAS, Brylee Whitehead's noteworthy achievement is a tremendous source of
pride for her parents, Mark Whitehead and Julie Whitehead, her school, and her community;
and
SJR1131
017656
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Ms. Whitehead's dedication to excellence is clearly deserving of the
respect, admiration, and commendation of the members of this General Assembly; now,
therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we hereby commend and honor Brylee Whitehead
on being named a 2026 Lewis County High School Top Ten Senior, salute her impressive
academic achievement, and extend to her our best wishes for a happy, successful future.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
